messages.message:
Alright, my second extra goal is done: we now have a doc outlining what outside dependencies (e.g. existing apps, projects, or deployments) each Cypress test needs (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1EgbRiQijxrYqSvvN7Bd97r-px-5JcQeizExNh3UoiOU/edit)! We no longer have to fear spinning up new testing environments or accidentally deleting stuff, probably.
I covered dependencies, schema for those dependencies, users, and env variables. We can add more if I forgot anything else that's important.
This is great!! We can also use this to determine which tests we can run as a health check for new deployments... and maybe try to reduce the tests that do have dependencies?!

That was a nice surprise for me when going over this - I saw how many tests that we've made to work without dependencies!
The vast majority of the remainder are app / deployment related, or are things that we can remove dependencies for
